</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-287_"><b>Best practice</b> - Continuous professional development that includes training on the effects of comorbidities and medications on clinical observations is crucial in geriatric care. Understanding the nuances of ageing physiology can significantly enhance the quality of care for elderly patients.
